      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FEDERAL FELIX (1) scored two back in the fastest time of the program when on speed but last start drifted back and wound up strongly to finish a 3.5 lengths third at The Gardens (30.09). Sure to be about the mark. NOVA REIGN (7) ran below best last time finishing fourth (30.31) over 520m at Wentworth Park in a Grade 5. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. Likely to play a prominent role. PACIFIC TIGER (2) had a low draw last time over 515m at this track but was in traffic and fell. Safe beginner and drawn well close to the inside. May be worth another try. REBORN SPARK (8) was out of placings last time (18.63) at Richmond in a NG, finishing eighth and beaten 9 lengths. Has already won two times from this draw.",
